IN THE MATTER OF THE ESTATE OF MARY McFEELY, DECEASED. Superior Court of New Jersey Appellate Division Argued January 29, 1951 — Decided February 6, 1951.

*522Before Judges Freund, Proctor and Rogers.

Mr. Abraham, J. Slurzberg argued the cause for the appellant (Mr. Joseph B. McFeely, executor of the last will and testament of Bernard M. McFeely, and attorney pro se). Mr. Victor S. Kilkenny argued the cause for the plaintiff-respondent (Messrs. Otis & Kilkenny, attorneys). Per Curiam.

The judgment is affirmed for the reasons expressed in the opinion of Judge Stanton in the court below.
